Demo GGPairs and Frequency Table

Nyssa Tucker

2023-02-06

1 Goal

Demonstrate several variables with multiple overlapping demo tables

2 Make data

I don’t have the actual data but I’d like to generate a dataframe to be used to show how ggpairs is useful.

2.1

2.2 small data

df <- tibble(
  a = rnorm(n = 20, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  b = rnorm(n = 20, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  c = rnorm(n = 20, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  d = rnorm(n = 20, mean = 0, sd = 1)
)

df2 <- df %>% pivot_longer(cols=c(1:4))
df2$smoker <- sample(c(0,1),size=80,replace=TRUE)
df2$female <- sample(c(0,1),size=80,replace=TRUE)
df2$black <- sample(c(0,1),size=80,replace=TRUE)
df2$threshold  <- ifelse(df2$value >= median(df2$value), 1,0
)

2.3 larger data

dfb <- tibble(
  a = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  b = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  c = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  d = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  e = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  f = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  g = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
  h = rnorm(n = 80, mean = 0, sd = 1),
)

df3 <- df2 %>% cbind(dfb)
